INSERT INTO `jrverses2018` (`id`, `ref`, `verse`) VALUES
(1, 'Gal1:1', 'Paul, an apostle, (not of men, neither by man, but by Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from the dead;)'),
(2, 'Gal1:2', 'And all the brethren which are with me, unto the churches of Galatia:'),
(3, 'Gal1:3', 'Grace be to you and peace from God the Father, and from our Lord Jesus Christ,'),
(4, 'Gal1:4', 'Who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us from this present evil world, according to the will of God and our Father:'),
(5, 'Gal1:5', 'To whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.'),
(6, 'Gal1:6', 'I marvel that ye are so soon removed from him that called you into the grace of Christ unto another gospel:'),
(7, 'Gal1:7', 'Which is not another; but there be some that trouble you, and would pervert the gospel of Christ.'),
(8, 'Gal1:8', 'But though we, or an angel from heaven, preach any other gospel unto you than that which we have preached unto you, let him be accursed.'),
(9, 'Gal1:9', 'As we said before, so say I now again, If any man preach any other gospel unto you than that ye have received, let him be accursed.'),
(10, 'Gal1:10', 'For do I now persuade men, or God? or do I seek to please men? for if I yet pleased men, I should not be the servant of Christ.'),
(11, 'Gal1:11', 'But I certify you, brethren, that the gospel which was preached of me is not after man.'),
(12, 'Gal1:12', 'For I neither received it of man, neither was I taught it, but by the revelation of Jesus Christ.'),
(13, 'Gal1:13', 'For ye have heard of my conversation in time past in the Jews\' religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the church of God, and wasted it:'),
(14, 'Gal1:14', 'And profited in the Jews\' religion above many my equals in mine own nation, being more exceedingly zealous of the traditions of my fathers.'),
(15, 'Gal1:15', 'But when it pleased God, who separated me from my mother\'s womb, and called me by his grace,'),
(16, 'Gal1:16', 'To reveal his Son in me, that I might preach him among the heathen; immediately I conferred not with flesh and blood:'),
(17, 'Gal1:17', 'Neither went I up to Jerusalem to them which were apostles before me; but I went into Arabia, and returned again unto Damascus.'),
(18, 'Gal1:18', 'Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to see Peter, and abode with him fifteen days.'),
(19, 'Gal1:19', 'But other of the apostles saw I none, save James the Lord\'s brother.'),
(20, 'Gal1:20', 'Now the things which I write unto you, behold, before God, I lie not.'),
(21, 'Gal1:21', 'Afterwards I came into the regions of Syria and Cilicia;'),
(22, 'Gal1:22', 'And was unknown by face unto the churches of Judaea which were in Christ:'),
(23, 'Gal1:23', 'But they had heard only, That he which persecuted us in times past now preacheth the faith which once he destroyed.'),
(24, 'Gal1:24', 'And they glorified God in me.'),
(25, 'Gal2:1', 'Then fourteen years after I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, and took Titus with me also.'),
(26, 'Gal2:2', 'And I went up by revelation, and communicated unto them that gospel which I preach among the Gentiles, but privately to them which were of reputation, lest by any means I should run, or had run, in vain.'),
(27, 'Gal2:3', 'But neither Titus, who was with me, being a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised:'),
(28, 'Gal2:4', 'And that because of false brethren unawares brought in, who came in privily to spy out our liberty which we have in Christ Jesus, that they might bring us into bondage:'),
(29, 'Gal2:5', 'To whom we gave place by subjection, no, not for an hour; that the truth of the gospel might continue with you.'),
(30, 'Gal2:6', 'But of these who seemed to be somewhat, (whatsoever they were, it maketh no matter to me: God accepteth no man\'s person:) for they who seemed to be somewhat in conference added nothing to me:'),
(31, 'Gal2:7', 'But contrariwise, when they saw that the gospel of the uncircumcision was committed unto me, as the gospel of the circumcision was unto Peter;'),
(32, 'Gal2:8', '(For he that wrought effectually in Peter to the apostleship of the circumcision, the same was mighty in me toward the Gentiles:)'),
(33, 'Gal2:9', 'And when James, Cephas, and John, who seemed to be pillars, perceived the grace that was given unto me, they gave to me and Barnabas the right hands of fellowship; that we should go unto the heathen, and they unto the circumcision.'),
(34, 'Gal2:10', 'Only they would that we should remember the poor; the same which I also was forward to do.'),
(35, 'Gal2:11', 'But when Peter was come to Antioch, I withstood him to the face, because he was to be blamed.'),
(36, 'Gal2:12', 'For before that certain came from James, he did eat with the Gentiles: but when they were come, he withdrew and separated himself, fearing them which were of the circumcision.'),
(37, 'Gal2:13', 'And the other Jews dissembled likewise with him; insomuch that Barnabas also was carried away with their dissimulation.'),
(38, 'Gal2:14', 'But when I saw that they walked not uprightly according to the truth of the gospel, I said unto Peter before them all, If thou, being a Jew, livest after the manner of Gentiles, and not as do the Jews, why compellest thou the Gentiles to live as do the Jews?'),
(39, 'Gal2:15', 'We who are Jews by nature, and not sinners of the Gentiles,'),
(40, 'Gal2:16', 'Knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law, but by the faith of Jesus Christ, even we have believed in Jesus Christ, that we might be justified by the faith of Christ, and not by the works of the law: for by the works of the law shall no flesh be justified.'),
(41, 'Gal2:17', 'But if, while we seek to be justified by Christ, we ourselves also are found sinners, is therefore Christ the minister of sin? God forbid.'),
(42, 'Gal2:18', 'For if I build again the things which I destroyed, I make myself a transgressor.'),
(43, 'Gal2:19', 'For I through the law am dead to the law, that I might live unto God.'),
(44, 'Gal2:20', 'I am crucified with Christ: nevertheless I live; yet not I, but Christ liveth in me: and the life which I now live in the flesh I live by the faith of the Son of God, who loved me, and gave himself for me.'),
(45, 'Gal2:21', 'I do not frustrate the grace of God: for if righteousness come by the law, then Christ is dead in vain.'),
(46, 'Gal3:1', 'O foolish Galatians, who hath bewitched you, that ye should not obey the truth, before whose eyes Jesus Christ hath been evidently set forth, crucified among you?'),
(47, 'Gal3:2', 'This only would I learn of you, Received ye the Spirit by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?'),
(48, 'Gal3:3', 'Are ye so foolish? having begun in the Spirit, are ye now made perfect by the flesh?'),
(49, 'Gal3:4', 'Have ye suffered so many things in vain? if it be yet in vain.'),
(50, 'Gal3:5', 'He therefore that ministereth to you the Spirit, and worketh miracles among you, doeth he it by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?'),
(51, 'Gal3:6', 'Even as Abraham believed God, and it was accounted to him for righteousness.'),
(52, 'Gal3:7', 'Know ye therefore that they which are of faith, the same are the children of Abraham.'),
(53, 'Gal3:8', 'And the scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the heathen through faith, preached before the gospel unto Abraham, saying, In thee shall all nations be blessed.'),
(54, 'Gal3:9', 'So then they which be of faith are blessed with faithful Abraham.'),
(55, 'Gal3:10', 'For as many as are of the works of the law are under the curse: for it is written, Cursed is every one that continueth not in all things which are written in the book of the law to do them.'),
(56, 'Gal3:11', 'But that no man is justified by the law in the sight of God, it is evident: for, The just shall live by faith.'),
(57, 'Gal3:12', 'And the law is not of faith: but, The man that doeth them shall live in them.'),
(58, 'Gal3:13', 'Christ hath redeemed us from the curse of the law, being made a curse for us: for it is written, Cursed is every one that hangeth on a tree:'),
(59, 'Gal3:14', 'That the blessing of Abraham might come on the Gentiles through Jesus Christ; that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.'),
(60, 'Gal3:15', 'Brethren, I speak after the manner of men; Though it be but a man\'s covenant, yet if it be confirmed, no man disannulleth, or addeth thereto.'),
(61, 'Gal3:16', 'Now to Abraham and his seed were the promises made. He saith not, And to seeds, as of many; but as of one, And to thy seed, which is Christ.'),
(62, 'Gal3:17', 'And this I say, that the covenant, that was confirmed before of God in Christ, the law, which was four hundred and thirty years after, cannot disannul, that it should make the promise of none effect.'),
(63, 'Gal3:18', 'For if the inheritance be of the law, it is no more of promise: but God gave it to Abraham by promise.'),
(64, 'Gal3:19', 'Wherefore then serveth the law? It was added because of transgressions, till the seed should come to whom the promise was made; and it was ordained by angels in the hand of a mediator.'),
(65, 'Gal3:20', 'Now a mediator is not a mediator of one, but God is one.'),
(66, 'Gal3:21', 'Is the law then against the promises of God? God forbid: for if there had been a law given which could have given life, verily righteousness should have been by the law.'),
(67, 'Gal3:22', 'But the scripture hath concluded all under sin, that the promise by faith of Jesus Christ might be given to them that believe.'),
(68, 'Gal3:23', 'But before faith came, we were kept under the law, shut up unto the faith which should afterwards be revealed.'),
(69, 'Gal3:24', 'Wherefore the law was our schoolmaster to bring us unto Christ, that we might be justified by faith.'),
(70, 'Gal3:25', 'But after that faith is come, we are no longer under a schoolmaster.'),
(71, 'Gal3:26', 'For ye are all the children of God by faith in Christ Jesus.'),
(72, 'Gal3:27', 'For as many of you as have been baptized into Christ have put on Christ.'),
(73, 'Gal3:28', 'There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither bond nor free, there is neither male nor female: for ye are all one in Christ Jesus.'),
(74, 'Gal3:29', 'And if ye be Christ\'s, then are ye Abraham\'s seed, and heirs according to the promise.'),
(75, 'Gal4:1', 'Now I say, That the heir, as long as he is a child, differeth nothing from a servant, though he be lord of all;'),
(76, 'Gal4:2', 'But is under tutors and governors until the time appointed of the father.'),
(77, 'Gal4:3', 'Even so we, when we were children, were in bondage under the elements of the world:'),
(78, 'Gal4:4', 'But when the fulness of the time was come, God sent forth his Son, made of a woman, made under the law,'),
(79, 'Gal4:5', 'To redeem them that were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of sons.'),
(80, 'Gal4:6', 'And because ye are sons, God hath sent forth the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying, Abba, Father.'),
(81, 'Gal4:7', 'Wherefore thou art no more a servant, but a son; and if a son, then an heir of God through Christ.'),
(82, 'Gal4:8', 'Howbeit then, when ye knew not God, ye did service unto them which by nature are no gods.'),
(83, 'Gal4:9', 'But now, after that ye have known God, or rather are known of God, how turn ye again to the weak and beggarly elements, whereunto ye desire again to be in bondage?'),
(84, 'Gal4:10', 'Ye observe days, and months, and times, and years.'),
(85, 'Gal4:11', 'I am afraid of you, lest I have bestowed upon you labour in vain.'),
(86, 'Gal4:12', 'Brethren, I beseech you, be as I am; for I am as ye are: ye have not injured me at all.'),
(87, 'Gal4:13', 'Ye know how through infirmity of the flesh I preached the gospel unto you at the first.'),
(88, 'Gal4:14', 'And my temptation which was in my flesh ye despised not, nor rejected; but received me as an angel of God, even as Christ Jesus.'),
(89, 'Gal4:15', 'Where is then the blessedness ye spake of? for I bear you record, that, if it had been possible, ye would have plucked out your own eyes, and have given them to me.'),
(90, 'Gal4:16', 'Am I therefore become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?'),
(91, 'Gal4:17', 'They zealously affect you, but not well; yea, they would exclude you, that ye might affect them.'),
(92, 'Gal4:18', 'But it is good to be zealously affected always in a good thing, and not only when I am present with you.'),
(93, 'Gal4:19', 'My little children, of whom I travail in birth again until Christ be formed in you,'),
(94, 'Gal4:20', 'I desire to be present with you now, and to change my voice; for I stand in doubt of you.'),
(95, 'Gal4:21', 'Tell me, ye that desire to be under the law, do ye not hear the law?'),
(96, 'Gal4:22', 'For it is written, that Abraham had two sons, the one by a bondmaid, the other by a freewoman.'),
(97, 'Gal4:23', 'But he who was of the bondwoman was born after the flesh; but he of the freewoman was by promise.'),
(98, 'Gal4:24', 'Which things are an allegory: for these are the two covenants; the one from the mount Sinai, which gendereth to bondage, which is Agar.'),
(99, 'Gal4:25', 'For this Agar is mount Sinai in Arabia, and answereth to Jerusalem which now is, and is in bondage with her children.'),
(100, 'Gal4:26', 'But Jerusalem which is above is free, which is the mother of us all.'),
(101, 'Gal4:27', 'For it is written, Rejoice, thou barren that bearest not; break forth and cry, thou that travailest not: for the desolate hath many more children than she which hath an husband.'),
(102, 'Gal4:28', 'Now we, brethren, as Isaac was, are the children of promise.'),
(103, 'Gal4:29', 'But as then he that was born after the flesh persecuted him that was born after the Spirit, even so it is now.'),
(104, 'Gal4:30', 'Nevertheless what saith the scripture? Cast out the bondwoman and her son: for the son of the bondwoman shall not be heir with the son of the freewoman.'),
(105, 'Gal4:31', 'So then, brethren, we are not children of the bondwoman, but of the free.'),
(106, 'Gal5:1', 'Stand fast therefore in the liberty wherewith Christ hath made us free, and be not entangled again with the yoke of bondage.'),
(107, 'Gal5:2', 'Behold, I Paul say unto you, that if ye be circumcised, Christ shall profit you nothing.'),
(108, 'Gal5:3', 'For I testify again to every man that is circumcised, that he is a debtor to do the whole law.'),
(109, 'Gal5:4', 'Christ is become of no effect unto you, whosoever of you are justified by the law; ye are fallen from grace.'),
(110, 'Gal5:5', 'For we through the Spirit wait for the hope of righteousness by faith.'),
(111, 'Gal5:6', 'For in Jesus Christ neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision; but faith which worketh by love.'),
(112, 'Gal5:7', 'Ye did run well; who did hinder you that ye should not obey the truth?'),
(113, 'Gal5:8', 'This persuasion cometh not of him that calleth you.'),
(114, 'Gal5:9', 'A little leaven leaveneth the whole lump.'),
(115, 'Gal5:10', 'I have confidence in you through the Lord, that ye will be none otherwise minded: but he that troubleth you shall bear his judgment, whosoever he be.'),
(116, 'Gal5:11', 'And I, brethren, if I yet preach circumcision, why do I yet suffer persecution? then is the offence of the cross ceased.'),
(117, 'Gal5:12', 'I would they were even cut off which trouble you.'),
(118, 'Gal5:13', 'For, brethren, ye have been called unto liberty; only use not liberty for an occasion to the flesh, but by love serve one another.'),
(119, 'Gal5:14', 'For all the law is fulfilled in one word, even in this; Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.'),
(120, 'Gal5:15', 'But if ye bite and devour one another, take heed that ye be not consumed one of another.'),
(121, 'Gal5:16', 'This I say then, Walk in the Spirit, and ye shall not fulfil the lust of the flesh.'),
(122, 'Gal5:17', 'For the flesh lusteth against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh: and these are contrary the one to the other: so that ye cannot do the things that ye would.'),
(123, 'Gal5:18', 'But if ye be led of the Spirit, ye are not under the law.'),
(124, 'Gal5:19', 'Now the works of the flesh are manifest, which are these; Adultery, fornication, uncleanness, lasciviousness,'),
(125, 'Gal5:20', 'Idolatry, witchcraft, hatred, variance, emulations, wrath, strife, seditions, heresies,'),
(126, 'Gal5:21', 'Envyings, murders, drunkenness, revellings, and such like: of the which I tell you before, as I have also told you in time past, that they which do such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God.'),
(127, 'Gal5:22', 'But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, longsuffering, gentleness, goodness, faith,'),
(128, 'Gal5:23', 'Meekness, temperance: against such there is no law.'),
(129, 'Gal5:24', 'And they that are Christ\'s have crucified the flesh with the affections and lusts.'),
(130, 'Gal5:25', 'If we live in the Spirit, let us also walk in the Spirit.'),
(131, 'Gal5:26', 'Let us not be desirous of vain glory, provoking one another, envying one another.'),
(132, 'Gal6:1', 'Brethren, if a man be overtaken in a fault, ye which are spiritual, restore such an one in the spirit of meekness; considering thyself, lest thou also be tempted.'),
(133, 'Gal6:2', 'Bear ye one another\'s burdens, and so fulfil the law of Christ.'),
(134, 'Gal6:3', 'For if a man think himself to be something, when he is nothing, he deceiveth himself.'),
(135, 'Gal6:4', 'But let every man prove his own work, and then shall he have rejoicing in himself alone, and not in another.'),
(136, 'Gal6:5', 'For every man shall bear his own burden.'),
(137, 'Gal6:6', 'Let him that is taught in the word communicate unto him that teacheth in all good things.'),
(138, 'Gal6:7', 'Be not deceived; God is not mocked: for whatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap.'),
(139, 'Gal6:8', 'For he that soweth to his flesh shall of the flesh reap corruption; but he that soweth to the Spirit shall of the Spirit reap life everlasting.'),
(140, 'Gal6:9', 'And let us not be weary in well doing: for in due season we shall reap, if we faint not.'),
(141, 'Gal6:10', 'As we have therefore opportunity, let us do good unto all men, especially unto them who are of the household of faith.'),
(142, 'Gal6:11', 'Ye see how large a letter I have written unto you with mine own hand.'),
(143, 'Heb1:1', 'God, who at sundry times and in divers manners spake in time past unto the fathers by the prophets,'),
(144, 'Heb1:2', 'Hath in these last days spoken unto us by his Son, whom he hath appointed heir of all things, by whom also he made the worlds;'),
(145, 'Heb1:3', 'Who being the brightness of his glory, and the express image of his person, and upholding all things by the word of his power, when he had by himself purged our sins, sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high;'),
(146, 'Heb1:4', 'Being made so much better than the angels, as he hath by inheritance obtained a more excellent name than they.'),
(147, 'Heb1:5', 'For unto which of the angels said he at any time, Thou art my Son, this day have I begotten thee? And again, I will be to him a Father, and he shall be to me a Son?'),
(148, 'Heb1:6', 'And again, when he bringeth in the firstbegotten into the world, he saith, And let all the angels of God worship him.'),
(149, 'Heb1:7', 'And of the angels he saith, Who maketh his angels spirits, and his ministers a flame of fire.'),
(150, 'Heb1:8', 'But unto the Son he saith, Thy throne, O God, is for ever and ever: a sceptre of righteousness is the sceptre of thy kingdom.'),
(151, 'Heb1:9', 'Thou hast loved righteousness, and hated iniquity; therefore God, even thy God, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness above thy fellows.'),
(152, 'Heb1:10', 'And, Thou, Lord, in the beginning hast laid the foundation of the earth; and the heavens are the works of thine hands:'),
(153, 'Heb1:11', 'They shall perish; but thou remainest; and they all shall wax old as doth a garment;'),
(154, 'Heb1:12', 'And as a vesture shalt thou fold them up, and they shall be changed: but thou art the same, and thy years shall not fail.'),
(155, 'Heb1:13', 'But to which of the angels said he at any time, Sit on my right hand, until I make thine enemies thy footstool?'),
(156, 'Heb1:14', 'Are they not all ministering spirits, sent forth to minister for them who shall be heirs of salvation?'),
(157, 'Heb2:1', 'Therefore we ought to give the more earnest heed to the things which we have heard, lest at any time we should let them slip.'),
(158, 'Heb2:2', 'For if the word spoken by angels was stedfast, and every transgression and disobedience received a just recompense of reward;'),
(159, 'Heb2:3', 'How shall we escape, if we neglect so great salvation; which at the first began to be spoken by the Lord, and was confirmed unto us by them that heard him;'),
(160, 'Heb2:4', 'God also bearing them witness, both with signs and wonders, and with divers miracles, and gifts of the Holy Ghost, according to his own will?'),
(161, 'Heb2:5', 'For unto the angels hath he not put in subjection the world to come, whereof we speak.'),
(162, 'Heb2:6', 'But one in a certain place testified, saying, What is man, that thou art mindful of him? or the son of man, that thou visitest him?'),
(163, 'Heb2:7', 'Thou madest him a little lower than the angels; thou crownedst him with glory and honour, and didst set him over the works of thy hands:'),
(164, 'Heb2:8', 'Thou hast put all things in subjection under his feet. For in that he put all in subjection under him, he left nothing that is not put under him. But now we see not yet all things put under him.'),
(165, 'Heb2:9', 'But we see Jesus, who was made a little lower than the angels for the suffering of death, crowned with glory and honour; that he by the grace of God should taste death for every man.'),
(166, 'Heb4:9', 'There remaineth therefore a rest to the people of God.'),
(167, 'Heb4:10', 'For he that is entered into his rest, he also hath ceased from his own works, as God did from his.'),
(168, 'Heb4:11', 'Let us labour therefore to enter into that rest, lest any man fall after the same example of unbelief.'),
(169, 'Heb4:12', 'For the word of God is quick, and powerful, and sharper than any twoedged sword, piercing even to the dividing asunder of soul and spirit, and of the joints and marrow, and is a discerner of the thoughts and intents of the heart.'),
(170, 'Heb4:13', 'Neither is there any creature that is not manifest in his sight: but all things are naked and opened unto the eyes of him with whom we have to do.'),
(171, 'Heb4:14', 'Seeing then that we have a great high priest, that is passed into the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast our profession.'),
(172, 'Heb4:15', 'For we have not an high priest which cannot be touched with the feeling of our infirmities; but was in all points tempted like as we are, yet without sin.'),
(173, 'Heb4:16', 'Let us therefore come boldly unto the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy, and find grace to help in time of need.'),
(174, 'Heb6:1', 'Therefore leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on unto perfection; not laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God,'),
(175, 'Heb6:2', 'Of the doctrine of baptisms, and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.'),
(176, 'Heb6:3', 'And this will we do, if God permit.'),
(177, 'Heb6:4', 'For it is impossible for those who were once enlightened, and have tasted of the heavenly gift, and were made partakers of the Holy Ghost,'),
(178, 'Heb6:5', 'And have tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the world to come,'),
(179, 'Heb6:6', 'If they shall fall away, to renew them again unto repentance; seeing they crucify to themselves the Son of God afresh, and put him to an open shame.'),
(180, 'Heb6:7', 'For the earth which drinketh in the rain that cometh oft upon it, and bringeth forth herbs meet for them by whom it is dressed, receiveth blessing from God:'),
(181, 'Heb6:8', 'But that which beareth thorns and briers is rejected, and is nigh unto cursing; whose end is to be burned.'),
(182, 'Heb6:9', 'But, beloved, we are persuaded better things of you, and things that accompany salvation, though we thus speak.'),
(183, 'Heb6:10', 'For God is not unrighteous to forget your work and labour of love, which ye have showed toward his name, in that ye have ministered to the saints, and do minister.'),
(184, 'Heb6:11', 'And we desire that every one of you do show the same diligence to the full assurance of hope unto the end:'),
(185, 'Heb6:12', 'That ye be not slothful, but followers of them who through faith and patience inherit the promises.'),
(186, 'Heb8:7', 'For if that first covenant had been faultless, then should no place have been sought for the second.'),
(187, 'Heb8:8', 'For finding fault with them, he saith, Behold, the days come, saith the Lord, when I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah:'),
(188, 'Heb8:9', 'Not according to the covenant that I made with their fathers in the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt; because they continued not in my covenant, and I regarded them not, saith the Lord.'),
(189, 'Heb8:10', 'For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, saith the Lord; I will put my laws into their mind, and write them in their hearts: and I will be to them a God, and they shall be to me a people:'),
(190, 'Heb8:11', 'And they shall not teach every man his neighbour, and every man his brother, saying, Know the Lord: for all shall know me, from the least to the greatest.'),
(191, 'Heb8:12', 'For I will be merciful to their unrighteousness, and their sins and their iniquities will I remember no more.'),
(192, 'Heb8:13', 'In that he saith, A new covenant, he hath made the first old. Now that which decayeth and waxeth old is ready to vanish away.'),
(193, 'Heb9:11', 'But Christ being come an high priest of good things to come, by a greater and more perfect tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not of this building;'),
(194, 'Heb9:12', 'Neither by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own blood he entered in once into the holy place, having obtained eternal redemption for us.'),
(195, 'Heb9:13', 'For if the blood of bulls and of goats, and the ashes of an heifer sprinkling the unclean, sanctifieth to the purifying of the flesh:'),
(196, 'Heb9:14', 'How much more shall the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without spot to God, purge your conscience from dead works to serve the living God?'),
(197, 'Heb9:22', 'And almost all things are by the law purged with blood; and without shedding of blood is no remission.'),
(198, 'Heb9:27', 'And as it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment:'),
(199, 'Heb9:28', 'So Christ was once offered to bear the sins of many; and unto them that look for him shall he appear the second time without sin unto salvation.'),
(200, 'Heb10:15', 'Whereof the Holy Ghost also is a witness to us: for after that he had said before,'),
(201, 'Heb10:16', 'This is the covenant that I will make with them after those days, saith the Lord, I will put my laws into their hearts, and in their minds will I write them;'),
(202, 'Heb10:17', 'And their sins and iniquities will I remember no more.'),
(203, 'Heb10:18', 'Now where remission of these is, there is no more offering for sin.'),
(204, 'Heb10:19', 'Having therefore, brethren, boldness to enter into the holiest by the blood of Jesus,'),
(205, 'Heb10:20', 'By a new and living way, which he hath consecrated for us, through the veil, that is to say, his flesh;'),
(206, 'Heb10:21', 'And having an high priest over the house of God;'),
(207, 'Heb10:22', 'Let us draw near with a true heart in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled from an evil conscience, and our bodies washed with pure water.'),
(208, 'Heb10:23', 'Let us hold fast the profession of our faith without wavering; (for he is faithful that promised;)'),
(209, 'Heb10:24', 'And let us consider one another to provoke unto love and to good works:'),
(210, 'Heb10:25', 'Not forsaking the assembling of ourselves together, as the manner of some is; but exhorting one another: and so much the more, as ye see the day approaching.'),
(211, 'Heb10:30', 'For we know him that hath said, Vengeance belongeth unto me, I will recompense, saith the Lord. And again, The Lord shall judge his people.'),
(212, 'Heb10:31', 'It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God.'),
(213, 'Heb10:35', 'Cast not away therefore your confidence, which hath great recompense of reward.'),
(214, 'Heb10:39', 'But we are not of them who draw back unto perdition; but of them that believe to the saving of the soul.'),
(215, 'Heb11:1', 'Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.'),
(216, 'Heb11:2', 'For by it the elders obtained a good report.'),
(217, 'Heb11:3', 'Through faith we understand that the worlds were framed by the word of God, so that things which are seen were not made of things which do appear.'),
(218, 'Heb11:4', 'By faith Abel offered unto God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, by which he obtained witness that he was righteous, God testifying of his gifts: and by it he being dead yet speaketh.'),
(219, 'Heb11:5', 'By faith Enoch was translated that he should not see death; and was not found, because God had translated him: for before his translation he had this testimony, that he pleased God.'),
(220, 'Heb11:6', 'But without faith it is impossible to please him: for he that cometh to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him.'),
(221, 'Heb11:7', 'By faith Noah, being warned of God of things not seen as yet, moved with fear, prepared an ark to the saving of his house; by the which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness which is by faith.'),
(222, 'Heb11:8', 'By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out into a place which he should after receive for an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing whither he went.'),
(223, 'Heb11:9', 'By faith he sojourned in the land of promise, as in a strange country, dwelling in tabernacles with Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise:'),
(224, 'Heb11:10', 'For he looked for a city which hath foundations, whose builder and maker is God.'),
(225, 'Heb11:17', 'By faith Abraham, when he was tried, offered up Isaac: and he that had received the promises offered up his only begotten son.'),
(226, 'Heb11:18', 'Of whom it was said, That in Isaac shall thy seed be called:'),
(227, 'Heb11:19', 'Accounting that God was able to raise him up, even from the dead; from whence also he received him in a figure.'),
(228, 'Heb11:20', 'By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things to come.'),
(229, 'Heb11:21', 'By faith Jacob, when he was a dying, blessed both the sons of Joseph; and worshipped, leaning upon the top of his staff.'),
(230, 'Heb11:22', 'By faith Joseph, when he died, made mention of the departing of the children of Israel; and gave commandment concerning his bones.'),
(231, 'Heb11:23', 'By faith Moses, when he was born, was hid three months of his parents, because they saw he was a proper child; and they were not afraid of the king\'s commandment.'),
(232, 'Heb11:24', 'By faith Moses, when he was come to years, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh\'s daughter;'),
(233, 'Heb11:25', 'Choosing rather to suffer affliction with the people of God, than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a season;'),
(234, 'Heb11:26', 'Esteeming the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures in Egypt: for he had respect unto the recompense of the reward.'),
(235, 'Heb11:27', 'By faith he forsook Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king: for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible.'),
(236, 'Heb11:28', 'Through faith he kept the passover, and the sprinkling of blood, lest he that destroyed the firstborn should touch them.'),
(237, 'Heb11:29', 'By faith they passed through the Red sea as by dry land: which the Egyptians assaying to do were drowned.'),
(238, 'Heb11:30', 'By faith the walls of Jericho fell down, after they were compassed about seven days.'),
(239, 'Heb11:31', 'By faith the harlot Rahab perished not with them that believed not, when she had received the spies with peace.'),
(240, 'Heb11:32', 'And what shall I more say? for the time would fail me to tell of Gedeon, and of Barak, and of Samson, and of Jephthae; of David also, and Samuel, and of the prophets:'),
(241, 'Heb11:33', 'Who through faith subdued kingdoms, wrought righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of lions,'),
(242, 'Heb11:34', 'Quenched the violence of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness were made strong, waxed valiant in fight, turned to flight the armies of the aliens.'),
(243, 'Heb11:35', 'Women received their dead raised to life again: and others were tortured, not accepting deliverance; that they might obtain a better resurrection:'),
(244, 'Heb11:36', 'And others had trial of cruel mockings and scourgings, yea, moreover of bonds and imprisonment:'),
(245, 'Heb11:37', 'They were stoned, they were sawn asunder, were tempted, were slain with the sword: they wandered about in sheepskins and goatskins; being destitute, afflicted, tormented;'),
(246, 'Heb11:38', '(Of whom the world was not worthy:) they wandered in deserts, and in mountains, and in dens and caves of the earth.'),
(247, 'Heb11:39', 'And these all, having obtained a good report through faith, received not the promise:'),
(248, 'Heb11:40', 'God having provided some better thing for us, that they without us should not be made perfect.'),
(249, 'Heb12:1', 'Wherefore seeing we also are compassed about with so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight, and the sin which doth so easily beset us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us,'),
(250, 'Heb12:2', 'Looking unto Jesus the author and finisher of our faith; who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and is set down at the right hand of the throne of God.'),
(251, 'Heb12:11', 'Now no chastening for the present seemeth to be joyous, but grievous: nevertheless afterward it yieldeth the peaceable fruit of righteousness unto them which are exercised thereby.'),
(252, 'Heb12:12', 'Wherefore lift up the hands which hang down, and the feeble knees;'),
(253, 'Heb12:13', 'And make straight paths for your feet, lest that which is lame be turned out of the way; but let it rather be healed.'),
(254, 'Heb12:14', 'Follow peace with all men, and holiness, without which no man shall see the Lord:'),
(255, 'Heb12:15', 'Looking diligently lest any man fail of the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up trouble you, and thereby many be defiled;'),
(256, 'Heb12:29', 'For our God is a consuming fire.'),
(257, 'Heb13:1', 'Let brotherly love continue.'),
(258, 'Heb13:2', 'Be not forgetful to entertain strangers: for thereby some have entertained angels unawares.'),
(259, 'Heb13:5', 'Let your conversation be without covetousness; and be content with such things as ye have: for he hath said, I will never leave thee, nor forsake thee.'),
(260, 'Heb13:6', 'So that we may boldly say, The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me.'),
(261, 'Heb13:7', 'Remember them which have the rule over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God: whose faith follow, considering the end of their conversation.'),
(262, 'Heb13:8', 'Jesus Christ the same yesterday, and to day, and for ever.'),
(263, 'Heb13:9', 'Be not carried about with divers and strange doctrines. For it is a good thing that the heart be established with grace; not with meats, which have not profited them that have been occupied therein.'),
(264, 'Heb13:15', 'By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of our lips giving thanks to his name.'),
(265, 'Heb13:16', 'But to do good and to communicate forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.'),
(266, 'Heb13:17', 'Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves: for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy, and not with grief: for that is unprofitable for you.'),
(267, 'Heb13:18', 'Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly.'),
(268, 'Heb13:19', 'But I beseech you the rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.');
